==English==

===Etymology===
Old English ''[[therfore]]''. See ''[[there]]'', ''[[fore]]'', and ''[[for]]'', and compare ''[[therefor]]''.

===Adverb===
'''therefore'''

# For that or this reason, referring to something previously stated; consequently; by consequence.
#:'''Quotations'''
#:*I have married a wife, and therefore I can not come. - [[Luke]], 14:20
#:*He blushes; therefore he is guilty. - [[Spectator]]
#[[for|For]] [[that]].
#:'''Quotations'''
#:*Behold, we have forsaken all, and followed thee; what shall we have therefore? - [[Matthew]], 19:27

